    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-01-21T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-01-21T19:00:00-05:00" n="798"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2331/53: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-01-21T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 21, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Your No. 4, January 14. You are requested to supply the Department by air mail
                    with as full information as possible regarding discriminatory treatment
                    resulting from decree of January 8. The Department assumes from your
                    communication that the suspension of higher import duties on woolen and cotton
                    textiles applies only in favor of Great Britain. I should be glad to know in
                    particular: First, is there any evidence that the British Government urged
                    discriminatory action? Second, if the suspension of higher duties on these
                    products is consolidated in the agreement with Great Britain, is it likely that
                    this concession will be extended to the United States? Third, can text of the
                    decree be secured?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
